race.comment: JENNI MULTABELLA (2) stalked the pace then was too good for a smart one in Polyglot on debut over 1106m at Sale back in July. Only public appearances since have been two recent Cranbourne jump-outs. Has 61kgs to contend with along with an extra 300m but she looks very smart and should cope. WOLFESS (5) returns from a 24-week break. Best form last prep was over middle distances, the highlight a win over 2000m at BM70 level. Could surprise while fresh on the back of a couple of recent jump-outs. GISELLA (9) tackled this trip for the first time last start and was fair through the line. Better for that run and drops in grade so worth another chance. QUEEN AMANJENA (8) missed the kick before rallying late to get up for third over 1300m at Cranbourne recently. Ready for another tilt at this distance. Last start Moe winner LAVENDER GLORY (3) looks ideally placed over more ground today.
